{"source_key":"sha256-31ae2543195c19275814384bf971ff26","record_index":526,"record_hash":"sha256:80b9a146497f24588949c357b217b3efb7668e291882168acfcb136cb008f52a","timestamp":"2026-05-25T07:54:23.580Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/upstream-crate-fixes.md\n@@\n | ID | Crate | Item | Sev | State |\n |----|-------|------|-----|-------|\n | B1 | but-agentlog | Public/read **projection API** (the load-bearing blocker) | 🔴 | ☐ |\n-| A1 | but-agentlog | Tag injected **sub-agent prompts** with provenance | 🔴 | ☐ |\n-| A2 | but-agentlog | Structured tool **exit code / outcome** (incl. crash vs check-fail) | 🟠 | ☐ |\n-| B6a | but-agentlog | **Entropy redactor eats path segments** | 🟠 | ☐ |\n+| A1 | but-agentlog | Tag injected **sub-agent prompts** with provenance | 🔴 | ☑ |\n+| A2 | but-agentlog | Structured tool **exit code / outcome** (incl. crash vs check-fail) | 🟠 | ☑ |\n+| B6a | but-agentlog | **Entropy redactor eats path segments** | 🟠 | ☑ |\n | A4 | but-agentlog | Keep **harness plumbing** out of the public projection | 🟡 | ☐ |\n-| A3 | but-agentlog | **Tool-kind** enum on records | 🟡 | ☐ |\n-| A5 | but-agentlog | Make **per-turn record truncation** observable | 🟡 | ☐ |\n+| A3 | but-agentlog | **Tool-kind** enum on records | 🟡 | ☑ |\n+| A5 | but-agentlog | Make **per-turn record truncation** observable | 🟡 | ☑ |\n | B3 | but-agentlog | **Bounded drill-down** via opaque record handles | 🟡 | ☐ |\n-| B5 | but-agentlog | Index **both review + branch** targets at capture | 🟡 | ☐ |\n+| B5 | but-agentlog | Index **both review + branch** targets at capture | 🟡 | ☑ |\n | B6 | but-agentlog | **Structured/labeled redaction markers** | ⚪ | ☐ |\n | B7 | but-agentlog | Expose **agent/provider label** in read output | ⚪ | ☐ |\n-| G1 | git-meta-lib | Faster / incremental **materialization** (cold-start cost) | 🟡 | ☐ |\n-| G2 | git-meta-lib | **Bare-repo / explicit object-DB** source (no checkout) | 🟡 | ☐ |\n+| G1 | git-meta-lib | Faster / incremental **materialization** (cold-start cost) | 🟡 | ◐ |\n+| G2 | git-meta-lib | **Bare-repo / explicit object-DB** source (no checkout) | 🟡 | ◐ |\n@@\n ### B1 · 🔴 Public/read projection API (the blocker) · ☐\n **Problem.** The crate is CLI-shaped. `lib.rs:11` exports only `Agent`, `Command`,\n `RelatedSessionTarget`, `run_from_dir`; the useful read types (session/turn timelines, record\n details) are `pub(crate)`. There's no library entry point that accepts PR/target facts and returns\n@@\n **Why.** Everything below rides on this; per the design, hosted public rendering is *blocked* on it.\n **Traces to:** Agent Trail doc 02 §B1.\n+**Codex note 2026-05-25.** Left open. I did not bolt a public API over the current CLI-shaped path;\n+that still needs a deliberately designed projection contract.\n \n-### A1 · 🔴 Tag injected sub-agent prompts with provenance · ☐\n+### A1 · 🔴 Tag injected sub-agent prompts with provenance · ☑\n **Problem.** Injected `spawn_agent` task prompts are stored with `role = \"user\"`, indistinguishable\n from real human input (`transcript.rs:118,170`). No `is_injected` / `prompt_source` field exists.\n **Fix.** At capture, detect `spawn_agent` and tag the resulting user record with a provenance enum\n@@\n **App-side mitigation:** Agent Trail heuristically filters injected prompts (27→20) and shows them as\n \"N sub-agent\" metadata — but it's guessing.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §A1; Agent Trail round-1 §4.\n+**Fixed 2026-05-25.** `but-agentlog` now stores `prompt_source = human | spawned_agent |\n+system_injected`, including Codex subagent sessions and prompts matched from `spawn_agent` calls.\n \n-### A2 · 🟠 Structured tool exit code / outcome · ☐\n+### A2 · 🟠 Structured tool exit code / outcome · ☑\n **Problem.** Tool results are opaque text — `\"Process exited with code 1\"`, `E0599`, test pass/fail\n live as free text inside `source_record`. No `exit_code`/`outcome`/`status` field\n (`transcript.rs:105` `RecordKind` has no outcome; `gitmeta/write.rs:468` has no status field).\n@@\n **App-side mitigation (shipped):** Agent Trail now treats could-not-execute codes (101/127) as\n indeterminate (`trail_projection.rs` `is_could_not_execute`) so a cargo crash no longer renders as\n \"fmt failed\" — but it's still scraping free text; the clean fix is a structured `outcome`.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §A2; round-3 P3-1.\n+**Fixed 2026-05-25.** Capture stores `exit_code` and `outcome = succeeded | failed |\n+could_not_execute`; cargo exit 101 is only `could_not_execute` when the text looks like an invocation\n+error, so real compile/check failures stay failed.\n \n-### B6a · 🟠 Entropy redactor fires inside filesystem paths, eating path segments · ☐\n+### B6a · 🟠 Entropy redactor fires inside filesystem paths, eating path segments · ☑\n **Problem.** Redaction runs at capture (`gitmeta/write.rs:121-128` via `redaction.rs`\n `redact_text`/`redact_value`, entropy- and key-based, marker `[REDACTED:entropy]`). The entropy\n heuristic matches a high-entropy **path segment** and removes it, so a doc path like\n@@\n **App-side mitigation:** Agent Trail coalesces adjacent redaction pills and covers `/tmp/` itself —\n but can't recover an eaten filename.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §B6a; round-2 P0-5.\n+**Fixed 2026-05-25.** Repo-relative paths are preserved through entropy redaction; absolute path\n+tokens redact as `[REDACTED:path]` instead of losing only a middle segment.\n@@\n **App-side mitigation (shipped):** Agent Trail strips these defensively — `is_plumbing_line` now\n covers `Process running`/`Process exited` (round-3) — but they ideally never enter the projection.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §A4/B2; round-3 P3-3.\n+**Codex note 2026-05-25.** Left open. This belongs in the B1 public projection; raw capture should\n+keep fidelity.\n \n-### A3 · 🟡 Tool-kind enum on records · ☐\n+### A3 · 🟡 Tool-kind enum on records · ☑\n **Problem.** `tool_name` is a raw string (\"Bash\", \"apply_patch\", \"spawn_agent\", \"write_stdin\",\n \"update_plan\", \"close_agent\"); no enum to group exec vs file-edit vs sub-agent vs housekeeping\n (`transcript.rs:105`).\n **Fix.** Add a `tool_kind` enum at capture or in the projection so both layers reason about\n signal-vs-noise consistently.\n **App-side mitigation:** Agent Trail classifies by name string (`classify_tool`).\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §A3.\n+**Fixed 2026-05-25.** Capture stores `tool_kind = exec | file_edit | sub_agent | housekeeping |\n+web_search | other`; read/detail output exposes it.\n \n-### A5 · 🟡 Make per-turn record truncation observable · ☐\n+### A5 · 🟡 Make per-turn record truncation observable · ☑\n **Problem.** When a read/show is capped, the caller can't tell a turn lost records. Agent Trail caps\n at `MAX_RECORDS_PER_TURN=512` and a turn that silently dropped tool activity is indistinguishable\n from a complete one.\n **Fix.** Return a \"more records exist / truncated\" signal from the read/show path (and from the B1\n projection), not just a silently-capped list.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §A5; round-2 C4.\n+**Verified 2026-05-25.** Existing read/show paths already return `RecordCoverage` with\n+`showing_records`, `total_records`, and `has_more_before`; timeline coverage has the same\n+`has_more_before` signal. B1 should carry this forward.\n@@\n **Fix.** Provide bounded exact-record reads through opaque handles (part of the B1 projection\n contract) so the UI can offer a \"raw record\" drill-down tier safely.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §B3.\n+**Codex note 2026-05-25.** Left open. Current drill-down still uses session/turn keys rather than\n+opaque public handles.\n \n-### B5 · 🟡 Index both review + branch targets at capture · ☐\n+### B5 · 🟡 Index both review + branch targets at capture · ☑\n **Problem.** agent-trail.md notes capture \"effectively picks the review id when present,\" so a\n PR-number lookup can miss the strongest evidence unless it falls back through the branch target.\n **Fix.** Capture/query so a branch carrying both `review_id` and `pull_request` indexes **both**\n useful targets.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §B5; agent-trail.md \"Repository And Hosting Boundary\".\n+**Fixed 2026-05-25.** Branch capture now indexes both `gitbutler-review:{review_id}` and\n+`pull-request:{branch_key}#{pull_request}` when both facts are present.\n@@\n **Problem.** Redaction emits inline string markers (`[REDACTED:entropy]`, `‹local path›`). The\n consumer can't reliably distinguish *kinds* of redaction to style them.\n **Fix.** Emit a structured/typed marker (kind = path | secret | …) rather than an inline string, so\n the UI can render labeled pills deterministically.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §B6; round-1 §4.\n+**Codex note 2026-05-25.** Left open. B6a improves the inline marker behavior, but this item asks\n+for typed redaction spans/markers, which is still projection/API work.\n@@\n **Why.** A reviewer wants to see which agent (Claude Code / Codex / …) did the work.\n **App-side mitigation:** Agent Trail *infers* the agent from tool fingerprints (shows \"Codex,\n inferred\") — a captured label would be authoritative.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §B7; agent-trail.md \"Show which agent(s)\".\n+**Codex note 2026-05-25.** Left open. Capture has agent metadata, but the public read/projection\n+shape still does not expose a clean label.\n@@\n-### G1 · 🟡 Faster / incremental materialization (cold-start cost) · ☐\n+### G1 · 🟡 Faster / incremental materialization (cold-start cost) · ◐\n **Problem.** Cold generation of an Agent Trail page is ~6s, dominated by GitMeta materialization +\n the many reads behind a skim/show pass (`Session::open` → `materialize` → per-turn reads). Warm\n reuse works, but first-hit latency is reviewer-facing.\n@@\n **Fix.** Investigate incremental/warm materialization and a batched read path so a projection doesn't\n pay per-turn open/query costs. (Shared concern with but-agentlog's read layer.)\n **App-side mitigation:** Agent Trail snapshot-caches by metadata OID + debounces the metadata fetch,\n so only the cold first hit is slow.\n **Traces to:** doc 02 §C3; Agent Trail round-1 §8 / caching work.\n+**Verified 2026-05-25.** Partial support already exists: `pull` skips materialization when the\n+tracking tip is unchanged and the store has been materialized, and `serialize` has incremental dirty\n+target handling. I did not change this item: cold materialization still parses full trees, and the\n+batched projection read path belongs with B1.\n \n-### G2 · 🟡 Support a bare-repo / explicit object-DB source (no checkout) · ☐\n+### G2 · 🟡 Support a bare-repo / explicit object-DB source (no checkout) · ◐\n **Problem.** The entry point is path/repository based: `Session::open(path)` opens a `gix::Repository`\n and materializes into `.git/git-meta.sqlite` next to a working repo; `but-agentlog::run_from_dir`\n rejects bare repositories. A hosted server must therefore create a **non-bare scratch repo with no\n@@\n **Fix.** A lower-level API that accepts an explicit object database / bare repo (or an in-memory\n GitMeta source) would let a hosted reader avoid materializing a full working repo. (Called out in\n agent-trail.md \"Server-Side Metadata Fetch\" as a separate library-design project.)\n **App-side mitigation:** Agent Trail initializes a non-bare scratch repo and fetches only\n `refs/meta/main`.\n **Traces to:** agent-trail.md \"Server-Side Metadata Fetch\"; Agent Trail repo-cache spike.\n+**Partially fixed 2026-05-25.** `git-meta-lib` now exposes `Session::from_repository(gix::Repository)`\n+for callers that already opened a repo with custom `gix` options, and tests verify `Session::open`\n+works against bare repositories with the SQLite store placed in the bare git dir. The larger\n+in-memory/object-DB-only source is still open, and `but-agentlog::run_from_dir` still has its own\n+bare-repo rejection.\n@@\n ### Changelog\n - **2026-05-25** — Created from Agent Trail review rounds 1–3 (doc 02 + rounds 06/07).\n - **2026-05-25** — Reviewed after the round-3 app-side fix pass: **no new upstream items**. The fixes\n   were app-side mitigations (A2 crash codes → indeterminate; A4 `Process running` strip) + a frontend\n   regression fix; all upstream root causes were already listed. Refreshed A2/A4 mitigation notes to\n   \"shipped.\"\n+- **2026-05-25** — Codex fix pass: fixed A1/A2/A3/B5/B6a in `but-agentlog`, verified A5 already\n+  exists, added a narrow `git-meta-lib` repository-handle constructor for G2, and left the B1/B3/B6/B7\n+  projection/API work open.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-25T07:54:23.580Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}